trim

public boolean trim(long size)
Trims the set table to a given expected number of elements.

This method is generally useful when reusing a set after clearing it, to avoid keeping in memory tables that are significantly smaller than required by the number of elements expected in the set.

Parameters:
size - the expected number of elements in the set
Returns:
true if the operation succeeded
